Description: Very small fragment of a seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration and partly a glossy surface. On the rear a small surface with organic impression (wood or leather?). The break is not cleaned and might have string impressions. The upper side is flat with the side bent downwards and shows a small part of an impression of an oval scarab-like seal with finger impressions visible around the seal impression. Recognisable is a very small cartouche in the lower left part, something like xaj mn(?) R'. Further signs outside of the cartouche but barely readable.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
